In task 2 (Build Your Student Digital Portfolio) , I chose three platforms which are :
 1. GitHub
 2. LinkedIn
 3. Kaggle

Now I am going to tell about each of these platforms and their uses -

1. GitHub is a platform that helps to manage and share coding projects efficiently .

It allows version control , collaboration and secure backup of files . 

Students can secure portfolios , contribute to open source projects and learn industry practices . 

Using GitHub improves teamwork, documentation skills, and coding discipline, making students better prepared for internships, placements, and real-world software development environments today itself .


2. LinkedIn is a professional networking platform that helps students connect with recruiters, professionals, and companies.

BTech students can create profiles to showcase skills, projects, and achievements. 

It allows job searching, internship opportunities, and learning through posts and courses. 

LinkedIn also helps in building a professional identity, expanding networks, and staying updated with industry trends for better career growth.


3.Kaggle is an online platform for data science and machine learning enthusiasts.

It provides datasets, coding notebooks, and competitions to practice real-world problems. 

Students can learn, collaborate, and improve skills in Python, data analysis, and AI. 

Kaggle also helps in building a strong portfolio, gaining recognition, and preparing for careers in data science and analytics


As a BTech student, I will use GitHub to upload projects, track progress, and collaborate with classmates. I will use LinkedIn to build a professional profile, connect with recruiters and explore internships. I will use Kaggle to practice data science, participate in competitions and learn from datasets. Over four years, these platforms will help me develop skills, build a portfolio, and improve career opportunities.


